                    <placeName xml:id="name11-8" xml:lang="en" source="#bib11-5">Qalʿat al-Madīq</placeName>
                    <desc xml:id="abstract-en-11" xml:lang="en">
                        <quote source="#bib11-1">One of the earliest Hellenistic city foundations in Syria, Apamea, situated on the Orontes ca. 90 km. south of Antioch, from the 2nd cent. onwards was an important center of Middle- and Neo-Platonist philosophy.</quote>
                    </desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="en">
                        <quote source="#bib11-1">38. Apamea</quote>
                    </desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="syr-Syrj">
                        <quote source="#bib11-3">ܡܕܝܢܬܳܐ ܗܘܳܬ ܪܰܒܬܐ ܕܰܠܓܰܪܒܰܝ ܡܰܕܢܰܚ ܚܡܳܬ ܘܚܰܪܝܒܳܐ ܗܳܫܐ ܘܡܶܬܐܶܡܰܪ ܠܗ̇ ܩܰܠܥܗ̈ ܐܠܡܨ̇ܝܩ.</quote>
                    </desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="ar">
                        <quote source="#bib11-4">مدينة كانت كبيرة في الشمال الشرقي من حماة وهي الآن خربة يقال لها قلعة المضيق</quote>
                    </desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="en">
                        <quote source="#bib11-5">once a large city northeast of Ḥama, it is now in ruins and is called Qalʿat al-Madīq.</quote>
                    </desc>
